pamsignal (0.2.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Packaging release: signed apt and dnf repositories published to
    GitHub Pages. The .deb binary is identical to v0.2.0; this release
    only adds the signing/distribution infrastructure plus the small
    spec fix that lets dnf 5 (Fedora 44) install the .rpm cleanly.

 -- Tuan Nguyen <anhtuank7c@hotmail.com>  Thu, 30 Apr 2026 11:00:00 +0000

pamsignal (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Align alert payloads with Elastic Common Schema (ECS). Breaking change
    to the chat text and JSON webhook formats — see CHANGELOG.md for the
    new schema and migration notes.
  * Chat text: severity-prefixed key=value (`[NOTICE] auth.login_success
    user=… pid=… ts=…`), with a new pid= field for direct `kill <pid>`.
  * JSON webhook: nested ECS objects (event.*, host.*, user.*, source.*,
    process.*) plus pamsignal.* for vendor-specific fields.
  * systemd-journal: ECS-aligned structured fields added alongside the
    existing PAMSIGNAL_* fields (kept through v0.2.x for backward compat).

 -- Tuan Nguyen <anhtuank7c@hotmail.com>  Thu, 30 Apr 2026 10:00:00 +0000

pamsignal (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging.
  * Six-phase OWASP 2025 / data-integrity / memory-safety audit closed every
    Critical, High, Medium, Low, and Info finding identified.
  * Alert dispatch hardened: secrets passed via memfd-backed curl config,
    not argv; absolute-path execv; --proto =https forced.
  * PID file via openat under O_DIRECTORY|O_NOFOLLOW dirfd; stale removal
    only after kill(pid,0) confirms ESRCH.
  * Per-source-IP brute-force cooldown.
  * Compiler hardening: _FORTIFY_SOURCE=3, stack-clash, CET, separate-code.
  * 78 CMocka tests across four suites; opt-in libFuzzer harness for the
    PAM message parser.

 -- Tuan Nguyen <anhtuank7c@hotmail.com>  Wed, 29 Apr 2026 16:10:00 +0000
